---
title: Peppercorn-Crusted Beef Tenderloin with Brussels Sprouts Amandine & Mashed Sweet Potatoes
description: If nothing says “date night” like a juicy steak, then this dish is the equivalent of getting down on one knee. Pan-seared, pepper-crusted steaks are topped with a chive-flecked butter (cue the swoons). But it’s not just any pepper, and it’s not just any steak: Here, freshly cracked peppercorns provide a spicy, crunchy coating for melt-in-your-mouth beef tenderloin. On the side, there’s crispy Brussels sprouts with toasty almonds, plus creamy mashed sweet potatoes. No matter who you cook this for, we have a good feeling they’ll be quite smitten.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66019655da283ecbc2883c27-931e36c1.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67169e6affa4e28ccb95eb30-en-US.pdf
course: main course
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/peppercorn-crusted-beef-tenderloin-67169e6affa4e28ccb95eb30
author: HelloFresh
